msgid "Networking Configuration with Systemd-networkd"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/network/common/systemd-network.xml:14
msgid "Network Interface Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/network/common/systemd-network.xml:16
msgid ""
"Udev may assign random Network Card Interface names for some network cards "
"such as enp2s1. If you are not sure what your Network Card Interface name "
"is, you can always run <command>ip l</command> after you have booted your "
"system. It is important that the <envar>Name</envar> variable in "
"<filename>/etc/systemd/network</filename> contain the correct Network Card "
"Interface name (e.g. <envar>Name=enp2s1</envar> or <envar>Name=eth0</envar>)"
" or systemd will fail to bring up your network interface."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><title>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/network/common/systemd-network.xml:27
msgid "Static Network Interface Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/network/common/systemd-network.xml:29
msgid ""
"<command>systemd-networkd</command> uses "
"<filename>/etc/systemd/network</filename> for configuration files. Refer to "
"systemd.network(5) and systemd.netdev(5). Configure a network interface with"
" a config file. Adjust Name= as required:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><screen>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/network/common/systemd-network.xml:34
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cd /etc/systemd/network &amp;&amp;\n"
"cat &gt; static.network &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"[Match]\n"
"Name=enp2s0\n"
"\n"
"[Network]\n"
"Address=192.168.1.1/24\n"
"Gateway=192.168.1.2\n"
"EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cd /etc/systemd/network &amp;&amp;\n"
"cat &gt; static.network &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"[Match]\n"
"Name=enp2s0\n"
"\n"
"[Network]\n"
"Address=192.168.1.1/24\n"
"Gateway=192.168.1.2\n"
"EOF</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/network/common/systemd-network.xml:44
msgid ""
"The values of these variables must be changed in every file to match the "
"proper setup."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/network/common/systemd-network.xml:47
msgid ""
"The <envar>Name</envar> variable defines the interface name, for example, "
"eth0. It is required for all network device configuration files."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/network/common/systemd-network.xml:51
msgid ""
"The <envar>Gateway</envar> variable should contain the default gateway IP "
"address, if one is present. If not, then comment out the variable entirely."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/network/common/systemd-network.xml:55
msgid ""
"For more information see the <command>systemd.netdev</command> man page."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><title>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/network/common/systemd-network.xml:60
msgid "Connecting to a network with DHCP"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/network/common/systemd-network.xml:62
msgid ""
"<command>systemd-networkd</command> uses "
"<filename>/etc/systemd/network</filename> for configuration files. Refer to "
"<filename>systemd.network(5)</filename> and "
"<filename>systemd.netdev(5)</filename>. Configure a network interface with a"
" config file. Adjust Name= as required:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><screen>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/network/common/systemd-network.xml:68
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cd /etc/systemd/network &amp;&amp;\n"
"cat &gt; dhcp.network &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"[Match]\n"
"Name=enp2s0\n"
"\n"
"[Network]\n"
"DHCP=yes\n"
"EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cd /etc/systemd/network &amp;&amp;\n"
"cat &gt; dhcp.network &lt;&lt; \"EOF\"\n"
"[Match]\n"
"Name=enp2s0\n"
"\n"
"[Network]\n"
"DHCP=yes\n"
"EOF</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/network/common/systemd-network.xml:77
msgid ""
"<command>systemd-networkd</command> will automatically configure "
"<filename>/run/systemd/network/resolv.conf</filename> when using DHCP.  If "
"you did not manually create <filename>/etc/resolv.conf</filename>, create a "
"symlink:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><sect3><screen>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/network/common/systemd-network.xml:82
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>ln -sv /run/systemd/network/resolv.conf /etc</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>ln -sv /run/systemd/network/resolv.conf /etc</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/network/common/systemd-network.xml:89
msgid "Using Timesyncd"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/network/common/systemd-network.xml:91
msgid ""
"Systemd includes a simple NTP client daemon, <command>systemd-"
"timesyncd</command>, though it is disabled by default. If you want to enable"
" it, you will first need to add a required user and group:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/network/common/systemd-network.xml:96
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>groupadd -g &gid-systemd-timesync; systemd-timesync\n"
"useradd -g systemd-timesync -u &uid-systemd-timesync; -d /dev/null -s /bin/false systemd-timesync</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>groupadd -g &gid-systemd-timesync; systemd-timesync\n"
"useradd -g systemd-timesync -u &uid-systemd-timesync; -d /dev/null -s /bin/false systemd-timesync</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/network/common/systemd-network.xml:99
msgid ""
"Then, actually enable <command>systemd-timesyncd</command> so that it will "
"run on system boot:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/network/common/systemd-network.xml:102
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>systemctl enable systemd-timesyncd</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>systemctl enable systemd-timesyncd</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: clfs-en/BOOK/network/common/systemd-network.xml:104
msgid ""
"You can configure <command>systemd-timesyncd</command> by editing "
"<filename>/etc/systemd/timesyncd.conf</filename>."
msgstr ""

